<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=roguebalance&message.id=2210#M2210">13</a> of 26
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 6952 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt list tab-stops: level1 mso-list: lfo1; l0 .25in? 0.25in; -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT:><SPAN **Zowie**?mso-list: Ignore?><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:></SPAN></FONT></FONT></FONT></SPAN><SPAN **Zowie**?mso-list: Ignore?>1.&nbsp; Move the Twisted Chance discipline&nbsp;to the Deadeye&nbsp;discipline&nbsp;timer.&nbsp;<SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></SPAN><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></P>
<DIV>-&nbsp;Twisted Chance(lvl 65)&nbsp;is on the same timer as Duelist(lvl 59), and&nbsp;the "supposed" upgrade to Duelist.&nbsp; While TC will outperform Duelist in certain situations, they are extremely rare. &nbsp;Duelist is still used over Twisted Chance by the <STRONG>vast</STRONG> majority of the rogues.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. Nerves of Steel AA is not working as intended. <SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>(Rashere is looking into fixing the description on this AA.&nbsp; QA is looking into sneak/hide being broken after a successful resist.)</FONT></SPAN> 
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>- Sneak/Hide is being broken even after a successful resist of an AE.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Additonally many rogues would like to see a change to the description of the AA so that its intended effect is more clear.&nbsp; Specifically the details concerning single target spells.</DIV>
<DIV><BR>&nbsp;</DIV></DIV>
<DIV>3. Implement&nbsp;a form of&nbsp;minor endurance preservation foci, or an&nbsp;endurance preservation&nbsp;foci that specificly effects the Assassin strike line of disciplines.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>- This issue is closely related to issue #4, and therefore could be combined in to one issue.&nbsp; Your discretion.</DIV></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: **Zowie**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN **Zowie**?mso-list: Ignore?><SPAN New ?Times Roman?? **Zowie**?FONT: 7pt>4.<FONT color=#000000><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;>Minimum bs damage should scale with weapon / Scale Chaotic Stab with weapon damage </SPAN><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:>(currently being evaluated)</SPAN></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: **Zowie**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: **Zowie**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: **Zowie**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: **Zowie**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;></SPAN></P><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;>5. &nbsp;Slightly increase the availability of tradable and single group weapons that allow more casual, unguilded, and/or non raiding rogues to stay relatively viable.<FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#ff0000 size=3> </FONT></SPAN><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:>(currently being evaluated)</SPAN><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;></SPAN></FONT></FONT></FONT> <FONT color=#0033cc>*Reworded*</FONT> 
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: **Zowie**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: **Zowie**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;>6. &nbsp; Assassin’s Strike is still not effective enough for the endurance cost,&nbsp; should be effective on double and triple bs if used when these work and damage cap made higher </SPAN><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:>(currently being evaluated)</SPAN><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;></SPAN></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: **Zowie**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: **Zowie**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;>Shroud of Stealth should make it so monsters see a rogue much more rarely then it does </SPAN><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#ff0000 size=3>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN 9pt; Verdana? COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;></SPAN></P>
<DIV><STRONG>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</STRONG>&nbsp; 8. Poisons<FONT color=#ff0000> (no change planned at this time)</FONT><FONT color=#0000ff> - perhaps a revision for the future on this</FONT></DIV>
<UL>
<LI>Integrate all old world poisons into the PoP poison system (including the ability to make 10 dose vials with&nbsp;the 10-15 min durations) 
<LI>Make poisons more viable by modifying the resist checks so they aren't so easily resisted. 
<LI>Add new, interesting, and more powerful &nbsp;poison recipes.&nbsp; Extremely powerful, but extremely rare poisons would be a nice addition. 
<LI>Add an upgrade to the poison mastery AA that would allow increased durations, effectiveness, and the ability to poison others weapons. 
<LI>Reduce the time investment required to collect components for lesser or more common poisons. Possibly through a better yield in combines or more components being made purchasable. 
<LI>Add the ability to poison thrown weapons.</LI></UL>
<P><STRONG>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</STRONG>9.&nbsp; Traps&nbsp;and lockpicking <FONT color=#0000ff><FONT color=#ff0000>(no change planned at this time)</FONT> - perhaps a revision for the future on this</FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI>Add &nbsp;the ability to permanently, or at least greatly increase the time that a trap stays disarmed after a successful attempt.&nbsp; This is the most tedious and irritating thing about traps.&nbsp; It's no fun to have to stand in the same place spamming a key to keep a trap disarmed.&nbsp; This would be a great AA. 
<LI>Add the ability to "see" traps via a target ring.&nbsp; Perfect idea for an AA. 
<LI>Add the ability to "mark" traps&nbsp;(once identified by a rogue) for others to see. Rogue specific or possibly raid/group leader AA. 
<LI>Make traps/locks have more of an impact in some (don't over do it ! =P)&nbsp;raid and group situations.&nbsp; If traps&nbsp;could be seen, and/or marked by a rogue, making them a lot more unforgiving would add an element of danger that a skilled rogue could take pride in overcoming. 
<LI>Add the ability to "set" traps after obtaining the highest level of trap AA (this would add signifcant&nbsp;value to an aa that is currently considered useless).&nbsp; Snare, DD's, root, dispel, etc.&nbsp; It could require tradeskill components (such as tinkering, smithing , or tailoring) to increase the usefulness of said tradeskills and help with balance. 
<LI>Allow rogues to identify/disarm ALL traps and pick any lock&nbsp;in LDoN.&nbsp; Rogues are the masters of these two abilities, not to mention they are class defining skills.&nbsp; Sharing the abilities with other classes isn't an issue, but reducing the effectiveness of our own makes absolutely no sense. </LI></UL>
<P>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 10. Improved corpse dragging. <FONT color=#0033ff>(NEW)</FONT><BR>&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This could be implemented through several means:<BR>&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Pre-consent&nbsp; - Allow players to tag other players with the ability to drag their corpse before death.<BR>&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Raid consent -&nbsp; Allow raid leaders to designate a set number of individuals with the ability to drag any corpse(indefinitely) within the raid.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Increase the number of corpses that can be drug at once.</P>
<P><STRONG>BUG: Fix the interaction (bug)&nbsp;between sneak/hide and Bard invis.</STRONG></P>
<DIV><STRONG>- This bug is not always specific to Bard songs. Some rogues have experienced the breaking of hide when a cast invis spell fades.</STRONG></DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Kytherea ~~wielding a giant hammer & a hairless War Hamster~~<br><br>"I'm late, I'm late...."
							</div>
								
