<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=roguebalance&message.id=3503#M3503">21</a> of 26
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 3512 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>1) Add more throwing items for rogues to use. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT> - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning </FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>- Lack of itemisation is preventing good use of the Deadly Aim discipline we received with OoW. <BR>- Throwing items must be summoned in order to be practical, along the lines of Ton Po's Mystical Pouch from Time. </FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>2) Enhance the Nerves of Steel AA so that it functions against single target spells as well (as is implied by the current description) or, failing that, refund the AA. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><FONT size=3><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"></SPAN></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>3) Improved critical hit AAs such as Veterans Wrath should apply to backstab. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>4) Minimum bs damage should scale with weapon / Scale Chaotic Stab with weapon damage. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT> - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning </FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>5) Slightly increase the availability of tradable and single group weapons that allow more casual, unguilded, and/or non raiding rogues to stay relatively viable. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) </FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>6) Assassin’s Strike is still not effective enough for the endurance cost. The endurance cost should be reduced to make it more in line with similar abilities of other classes. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>7) Implement a way for rogues to spot see-SoS mobs more easily; and a way for rogues to check whether a mob sees through regular invisibility<BR>- Mobs which do not see through Shroud of Stealth, but which see through invisibility, should give a message akin to "You suspect this being can see you" but which reads "Your stealth prevents this mob from seeing you"<BR>- Clicking and conning every mob sometimes isn't practical, especially in transit zones (on the way to a raid etc. where it is ridiculous to expect a rogue to con every mob); and mobs which see through Shroud of Stealth tend to be fairly unpredictable. It would be better to have some kind of visible marker so that mobs which see SoS can be more quickly identified and avoided, rather than just trained to the zoneline. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT> - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning </FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>8) Make poisons easier to use and less prohibitive in terms of time investment. Some suggestions of how to achieve this are: (currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning </FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>- Implement some form of endless poison or poison conservation AA. <BR>- Increase the drop rate of poison ingredients or make them purchaseable at a reasonable cost. <BR>- Increase the yield of poisons per combine. <BR>- Dramatically increase the yield of poisons per combine, making the poisons yielded no rent. <BR>- Make old world poisons stackable. </FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>9) Add more +backstab damage items at all levels of play.&nbsp; <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>10) Re-evaluate the focus effects on rogue armour sets from Qvic onwards.&nbsp;<FONT color=#ff0000> (currently being evaluated)</FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>- The armour sets appear to have been copy/pasted a lot rather than individually tailored for each class. This does not work well for rogues because our desires are so specialised.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #cccccc"><FONT size=3>- Many rogues are unhappy with the tier2 OoW breastplate from Anguish. See this </FONT><A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=roguebalance&amp;message.id=3011" target=_blank><FONT color=#fac400 size=3>discussion thread</FONT></A><FONT size=3>. </FONT></SPAN></P></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
