<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=roguebalance&message.id=3939#M3939">24</a> of 26
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2491 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		
				background-color: #050A0E; 
				
				 background-image: none;
				 
				background-repeat: repeat-x;
				" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV>1) Boost Sustained DPS <FONT color=#ffff00>(New)</FONT><BR>- Boost sustained DPS by ~5% either through the addition of triple attack or via backstab accuracy or damage increases so that we maintain a clear advantage over other classes in sustained DPS.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2) Timer Adjustments <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT><BR>- Move Assassin's Feint line off the Sneak Attack line timer .</DIV>
<DIV>- Move Twisted Chance to the Deadeye timer or its own timer.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3) Double/Triple backstab <FONT color=#ff0000>(No changes planned at this time)</FONT><BR>- Double/Triple backstab should function with Siezed Opportunity. <FONT color=#0000ff>(shack - specifically not supposed to)</FONT><BR>- Double/Triple backstab should be affected by the Sneak Attack line. <FONT color=#0000ff>(shack -&nbsp;note currently possible&nbsp;to implement)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4) Boost Burst DPS <FONT color=#ffff00>(New)</FONT><BR>- It's difficult for us to judge an appropriate change because of difficulty obtaining accurate data, but suggest either the addition of a new long re-use disc on a new timer or by moving twisted chance to the deadeye timer.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5) Illusions <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) </FONT><FONT color=#0000ff>(shack - new illusions added with DoDH)</FONT><BR>- Add more illusion masks for rogues at all levels of play.<BR>- Add illusion: Shadowman or similar "stealthy" appearance.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>6) Shroud of Stealth <FONT color=#ffff00>(New)</FONT><FONT color=#ffff00><BR></FONT>- Make it possible to identify mobs which see through SoS without conning them.<BR>- Some rogues feel there are too many see-SoS mobs in DoDH.<BR>- Zonewide AEs are increasingly common and break SoS for the entire zone.<BR>- The "Your Shroud of Stealth keeps you hidden" message doesn't appear to be functioning properly. It's been suggested that this is because the message doesn't function on undead mobs.<BR>- NPCs with whom players are supposed to talk in DoDH have helpfully been flagged as see-invis. They need to be flagged as see-SoS as well</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>7) Position Dependancy<FONT color=#ffff00> </FONT><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT><BR>- Out of Range / Cannot See should not blow backstab / sneak attack<BR>- Increase hitbox size of mobs, particularly on raid encounters<BR>- Fix the "cannot see" and "out of range" issues with backstab. Suggested that this is caused by client/server syncing. <FONT color=#ffff00>(New)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>8) Poisons <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT> <FONT color=#0000ff>- will most likely be considered as part of the class re-envisioning</FONT><BR>Make poisons easier to use and less prohibitive in terms of time investment. Some suggestions of how to achieve this are:<BR>- Implement some form of endless poison or poison conservation AA.<BR>- Increase the drop rate of poison ingredients or make them purchaseable at a reasonable cost.<BR>- Increase the yield of poisons per combine.<BR>- Dramatically increase the yield of poisons per combine, making the poisons yielded no rent.<BR>- Make old world and PoP poisons stackable<BR>- Add a resist adjustment for poisons via AAs or new poison recipes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>9) Itemisation<BR>- Add more +backstab damage items at all levels of play. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT><BR>- Please examine the effect of recent boosts to other classes in relation to rogues, bearing in mind that they are mostly not itemisation based, and thus may leave casual rogues with problems keeping up. <FONT color=#ffff00>(New)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>10) AE Rampage <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT><BR>- Add an additional defence for rogues to avoid AE rampage.</DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Kytherea ~~wielding a giant hammer & a hairless War Hamster~~<br><br>"I'm late, I'm late...."
							</div>
								
